<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-168-442  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 168 442.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  April 10 1989 v6 n14 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In effort to boost product line, Cipher merges with Irwin. (CipherInc.) (Irwin Magnetic Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Isaac, Daniel.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Irwin Magnetic Systems Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)Cipher Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    IRWN.andO;Topic:     Computer industryMergerTape Drives.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>In a merger analysts described as a natural, high-end tape-backup makerCipher Inc. last week put the final touches on a $75 million deal to buyIrwin Magnetic Systems Inc.andM;The merger stems from Irwin's fiscal difficulties after losing several OEMcontracts and following slow sales last year, and from Cipher's desire toenter the low-end, tape-backup market, where Irwin is a market leader.andM;Cipher, of San Diego, is a major supplier of high-end tape-backup products.andM;''It's a good move for both,'' said Robert Abraham, of Freeman Associates, aSanta Barbara, Calif., market researcher.andP;  ''[Their] product lines complementeach other.'' -- D.I.andO;</TEXT></DOC>